HEADWORD: Spad
<hw>Spad</hw> <pr>(sp⟦acr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mining)</fld>
<def>A nail one or two inches long, of iron, brass, tin, or tinner iron,
with a hole through the flattened head, used to mark stations in
underground surveying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

